help~
The demons eyes glow deep violet as it looks upon you, giving no hint as to
whether it would like to destroy you or entertain your questions... again your
mind is filled with its words... 'Hah!  If indeed you wish to help me in my
search, your reward will be great indeed mortal.  I am Rozkadrath, ambassador of
Joukarth Forgath, keeper and ruler of the 400th layer of the Abyss, punisher of
the damned.  The Nalfeshnee ruler has declared a war with the Balors and require
lost relics and components for a spell which will guarentee our victory over the
pitiful creatures.  I have been able to locate a few reagents, as the foolish
conjurer who summoned me was a collector of such things which my master
requires, but I am running out of time as the war is deeply under way.  If you
will assist his lordship in this task, I assure you you shall become more
powerful than any mortal has ever dreamed.  Can you assist me in this task?'
~
M
yes~
You feel a dark wave of energy pass over you as the dark voice rumbles within
your head 'Excellent.  Although I am sure you will assist Joukarth most
valiantly in his quest for dominance, I shall require you to prove your
obedience to my master before I trust you with such a an important task.  There
is a great many-armed demon who dwells within the Hell plane who is known to
possess great power.  I require the items of power which he possesses.  Bring me
these and Rozkadrath shall reward you'.  As quickly as they came, your mind is
freed from the demonic whispers.
~
Q
As you place the items before the demon a large flame erupts from the ground,
engulfing them in a blaze of hellfire.  As Suddenly as it came, the fire is
exstinguished.  A small circle of smoldering embers line the now barren earth
before you.  The demon's eyes focus on your head as the dominating voice plagues
your mind once again... 'Excellent mortal.  I see that you may infact possess
the power required to assist Joukarth in his quest.  Although I am not a master
of the arcane magics like my master Joukarth is, I do understand the inner
workings of the spell which he wishes to invoke.  It is elemental in nature, and
thus requires reagants which are pure and flawless.  Retrieve for me an earring
of solidified lightning and a cloak of swirling mists, its keeper being the one
who cannot be seen.  Take this seal as proof that you represent his highness
Joukarth Forgath and return it also to me when you have obtained the first of
the required reagents.  Go now mortal.'
~
